title: SFH visits Guangzhou (with photos)
content_text:
p>
    The Secretary for Food and Health, Dr York Chow, begins a two-day visit to 
    Guangzhou this afternoon (November 24). He will meet his Mainland 
    ministerial counterparts and tour the 16th Asian Games equestrian 
    competition venue. Dr Chow first went to the "equine disease-free" zone in Conghua City, 
    Guangzhou Municipality, to visit the Asian Games equestrian competition 
    venue and inspect the special quarantine and medical facilities for horses

venue and inspect the special quarantine and medical facilities for horses 
    competing in the Asian Games equestrian events.  The Asian Games equestrian events are the first international equestrian 
    events hosted in the Mainland. The Food and Health Bureau of the Hong Kong 
    Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) Government and the State General 
    Administration of Quality Supervision, Inspection and Quarantine (AQSIQ) had 
    earlier signed a collaboration agreement on equine inspection and quarantine

earlier signed a collaboration agreement on equine inspection and quarantine 
    for the equestrian events.  According to the agreement, both sides agree to work closely on various 
    aspects of the equestrian events, including the creation of the disease-free 
    zone, veterinary services, transportation of horses, stable and competition 
    venue management. The Agriculture, Fisheries and Conservation Department (AFCD) 
    of the HKSAR Government will give technical support and training to the 
    inspection and quarantine authorities of the Mainland under the agreement.

inspection and quarantine authorities of the Mainland under the agreement. 
    During the event period, the AFCD's experts will also assist Mainland 
    authorities in relation to the quarantine of participating horses, to ensure 
    the smooth running of the equestrian events of the 16th Asian Games. Dr Chow will also call on officials of the Guangdong Entry-Exit Inspection 
    and Quarantine Bureau to exchange views on issues of mutual concern, and to 
    foster co-operation between the two sides. Dr Chow will meet with officials of the Department of Health of Guangdong

Province and visit the Guang Dong Hospital of Traditional Chinese Medicine and other medical facilities in Guangzhou before returning to Hong Kong tomorrow evening (November 25). Ends/Wednesday, November 24, 2010
Issued at HKT 18:08
